	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've been playing with trying to fix this on and off for a long time, but it's just really getting on my nerves and it seriously needs to get fixed. So, there are multiple issues. Right now I'm most interested in fixing the most annoying one. Sometimes my square channels continue to output a high tone when they should be silent. It's pretty rare in a game, but I've got a chiptune NSF that I converted to a NES by zanzan that demonstrates it right at the beginning, and continues for the first 20 to 25 seconds of the song. I've attached a ZIP of the current win32 build (works in WINE too) of my emulator along with that NES ROM to play it so you can see what I mean. After the first part of the song, the rest of it sounds pretty much correct compared to other emulators.<br /><br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<span class="genmed">
				<img src="./styles/subsilver2/imageset/icon_topic_attach.gif" width="14" height="18" alt="" title="" /> 
